@node ToolTypes

@{FG Highlight}ToolTypes@{FG Text}
---------

DST		= Sets daylight saving time (DST). Use this ToolType if
		  you don't use one of the supported environment-variables.

SHOWGMT		= Shows you the GMT time in the window.

SHOWLOCAL	= Shows you the local time in the window.

TOP		= Window offset from top of the screen.

LEFT		= Window offset from left of the screen.


If you don't use TOP/LEFT tooltype, the window will be placed left to the depth
gadget.

@endnode

@node ARexx

@{FG Highlight}ARexx@{FG Text}
-----

ABeat supports a very simple ARexx-Port. The port's name is "ABEAT".
ABeat provides the following ARexx commands:


@{b}BEAT@{ub}		- returns the actual BEAT in RESULT.

@{b}DATE@{ub}		- returns the BMT Date in RESULT.

@{b}TIME@{ub}		- returns the local time in RESULT.

@{b}GMTTIME@{ub}		- returns the GMT time in RESULT.

@{b}ALARM@{ub}		- returns the wake-up BEAT in RESULT.

@{b}SET@{ub} <Beat>	- set the wake-up call to the given <Beat>.

@{b}ON@{ub}		- switches wake-up call ON.

@{b}OFF@{ub}		- switches wake-up call OFF.

@{b}ALARMGUI@{ub}	- opens the wake-up-time window.

@{b}STATUS@{ub}		- returns WARN if alarm-clock is OFF.

@{b}QUIT@{ub}		- quits ABeat.

You'll find the following example scripts in the release-archiv:

@{"ABeat.rexx   " link ABeat.rexx/MAIN}		- A script including all ABeat-ARexx-commands.
@{"Beat2Ced.ced " link Beat2Ced.ced/MAIN}		- includes BMT-Date and Beat to the cursor position.
@endnode

